<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1843,2015]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1843,1868]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[282,386,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hayesi">
<emphasis box="[282,386,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">L. hayesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar by wing pattern to previous two species, with wide black postmedial line curved inwards after M 
<number box="[335,343,1895,1909]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="3.0">3</number>
, both sides of the postmedial line bordered with black lines, however, the apex of this species lacks greyish-white patch. In the male genitalia, it is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[875,968,1920,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nama">
<emphasis box="[875,968,1920,1943]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">L. nama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by presence of small process on apex of valva, but the shape of saccus is different, and the outer margin of the saccus is arched but angled basally in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nama">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">L. nama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(followed 
<bibRefCitation author="Sugi" box="[336,454,1991,2015]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Sugi, S. (1982), Noctuidae. In: Inoue, H. et al. (Eds). Moths of Japan. Vol. 1 &amp; 2. Kodansha, Tokyo, Vol. 1, 669 - 913; Vol. 2, 344 - 405, pls. 164 - 223, 229, 355 - 382." type="book chapter" year="1982">
Sugi 
<number box="[394,454,1991,2015]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
